@startuml warning_beep_to_audio_focus_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Warning Beep To Audio Focus Signal Flow\n(Core / IVI -> CLU / AMP)

participant "Core / CoreState\nalert decision/effective state" as Core #FFF4CC
participant "IVI\npresentation + audio owner" as IVI #E8F0FE
participant "CLU\ncluster mirror consumer" as CLU #E8F7E8
participant "AMP\naudio ducking owner" as AMP #FFE6E6

== Warning / Presentation Inputs ==

Core -> IVI : selectedAlertEffectiveLevel / Type\nemergencyContext / timeoutClear
IVI -> IVI : derivePresentationMode()
IVI -> IVI : deriveAlertVolume()
IVI -> IVI : compatBeepEmergency / IC / Speed
IVI -> IVI : warningBeepState = any(beep*) > 0
note right of IVI
Key render/audio seams
- UiRender::beepEmergency
- UiRender::beepIC
- UiRender::beepSpeed
- UiRender::warningBeepState
end note

== Audio Focus Publication ==

IVI -> IVI : AudioFocusOwner = (alertLevel > 0 and presentationMode != 1) ? 1 : 0
IVI -> IVI : AudioDuckingLvl = (alertLevel > 0) ? 4 : 1
IVI -> CLU : frmAudioFocusMsg\nfrmMediaStateMsg
IVI -> AMP : frmAudioFocusMsg\nfrmMediaStateMsg

== CLU Mirror ==

activate CLU
CLU -> CLU : consume frmAudioFocusMsg
CLU -> CLU : mirror CoreState::audioFocusOwner\nCoreState::audioDuckingLvl
note right of CLU
CLU keeps a cluster-visible mirror
of the current audio focus and
ducking state for runtime review.
end note
deactivate CLU

== AMP Ducking Ownership ==

activate AMP
AMP -> AMP : consume media/focus/voice/tts frames
AMP -> AMP : expire stale inputs if needed
AMP -> AMP : baseVolume = deriveBaseVolume(Inject::alertVolumeCmd)
AMP -> AMP : ampDucking = max(audioDuckingLvl,\nvoice/tts floors)
AMP -> AMP : publish AmpMode / AmpDuckingLvl / AmpVolumeLevel
note right of AMP
Representative outputs
- CoreState::baseVolume
- UiRender::renderVolumLevel
- frmAmplifierStateMsg
end note
deactivate AMP

note over Core, AMP
Representative runtime chain
1. Core effective alert state reaches IVI
2. IVI derives beep flags and audio-focus frames
3. CLU mirrors focus state for cluster visibility
4. AMP turns focus/ducking into actual amplifier behavior
end note

@enduml
